    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Kyle Tucker**, who commands an elite 85.72 score against Tomoyuki Sugano. **Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park adjustment and a favorable matchup against a pitcher with a 4.69 xERA, making him our primary anchor. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** (79.50) and **Andy Pages** (75.58) provide substantial momentum. **Pages**, in particular, leverages the same park factors as **Tucker** to provide high-end production despite a neutral platoon setting. Meanwhile, **Drake Baldwin** (72.00) remains a strong play; his projection is bolstered significantly by a +19% boost from facing Taijuan Walker\u2019s hittable profile, assuming he settles into the #2 spot as anticipated.\n\nStrategic nuance defines our bench decisions, specifically regarding **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (60.17). While he remains a dangerous bat, he narrowly missed the cut behind the superior matchup efficiency of **Marcell Ozuna** and **Josh Lowe**. **Lowe** is a compelling \"start\" at 70.08, as he capitalizes on Matt Waldron\u2019s brutal 7.83 xERA; the optimizer favored the sheer volume of run-scoring potential in that specific matchup over the slightly higher base projection of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** against Michael Soroka. Elsewhere, **Jacob Wilson** (68.59) earns a spot due to a 10% park lift and favorable SP conditions. While **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Brady House** possess the speed profile we crave for 5x5 Roto, their sub-55 scores reflect the reality of today's matchups; **Luis Robert Jr.** specifically suffered from a sharp -15% platoon penalty, keeping him on the bench. \n\nRisks remain, primarily the reliance on \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the board. We are counting on **Miguel Vargas** and **Kyle Tucker** to lead off, and any shift in the order could disrupt their efficiency scores. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** presents the highest risk of the starters, as facing the elite arm of Logan Webb (3.14 xERA) yields a -19% SP skill penalty. However, his strong platoon advantage provides just enough cushion to justify his inclusion over our speed-heavy bench options like **Brady House**. We will continue to monitor weather and official lineups closely to ensure the Austin Waves capitalize on these projected favorable environments.",
